      "beast_baseline": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That \"human ingenuity\" stuff just feels like a cope to me. It's like people are trying to put a band-aid on a severed limb. Every time I see a new report about biodiversity loss or ocean warming, it just feels more and more certain that we've already crossed the point of no return. How can you even suggest \"actionable advice\" when the math just doesn't look good? It feels like we're just delaying the inevitable.",
